After his death and especially after the death of Terence in 159, when no new plays were being written, the theatre managers began to produce for a second time the plays of Plautus which they had in their possession. For such second presentations the plays were cut down in some soenes and expanded in others, and the prologues were in some cases (as the Casina) entirely rewritten.
